<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="321" pageId="4" pageNumber="320" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,932,1064]" box="[151,493,932,957]" pageId="4" pageNumber="320">Female. Body length: 3.0 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,932,1064]" pageId="4" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis box="[199,287,968,992]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="320">Colour:</emphasis>
head entirely black, palpi yellow, flagellum dark brown with five white flagellomeres near to apex, last three flagellomeres dark brown, scape yellow; mesosoma and metasoma all black; wing veins and stigma dark brown; all legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272062/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="320" targetBox="[227,1359,1117,1961]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1982,2036]" pageId="4" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,341,1982,2005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="320">FIGURES 15–18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[349,593,1983,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Heterospilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fernandesi">
<emphasis box="[349,593,1983,2005]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="320">Heterospilus fernandesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Holotype, female. 32, habitus, lateral view; 33, head, mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; 34, mesosoma, dorsal view; 35, metasoma, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="5" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis box="[199,260,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="321">Head</emphasis>
: vertex and frons smooth, face granulose; malar space greater than ¼ eye height; temple narrow, width less than ½ eye width; ocell-ocular distance 2.5 times the diameter of lateral ocellus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="5" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis box="[199,327,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="321">Mesosoma:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[340,485,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Heterospilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesopleuron">mesopleuron</taxonomicName>
granulose, precoxal sulcus smooth, shorter than width of 
<taxonomicName box="[1177,1326,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Heterospilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesopleuron">mesopleuron</taxonomicName>
; lobes of mesoscutum smooth and hairy just along notauli; notauli weak or absent, meeting prescutellar furrow in triangular costate area; prescutellar furrow with five cross carinae; scutellum smooth; propodeum with basal median areas distinct and margined, basal median areas smooth, basal median carina absent, areolar margin indistinct, areolar area areolate-rugose, lateral areas entirely rugose, mesosternum smooth. 
<emphasis box="[969,1084,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="321">Fore wing</emphasis>
: vein r shorter than vein 3 
<collectingCountry box="[1381,1432,368,392]" name="South Africa" pageId="5" pageNumber="321">RSa</collectingCountry>
, vein 1cu-a interstitial with vein 1M, stigma wider than length of vein r. 
<emphasis box="[969,1097,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="321">Hind wing:</emphasis>
vein SC+R present, length of vein M+CU shorter than vein 
<specimenCount box="[488,534,440,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="321" type="generic">1M.</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="5" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis box="[199,325,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="321">Metasoma:</emphasis>
first tergum longitudinally costate, apical width equal to length; tergum II costate, apical width 2.5–3 times length; third tergum costate at base with smooth apex; terga II+III with anterior transverse groove weakly present and sinuose; posterior transverse groove weak; terga IV–VII smooth; ovipositor equal to 3/4 length of metasoma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
